the Philippine National Police-Highway Patrol Group were manning a control point in Maligaya Drive, Brgy. Pasong Putik, Quezon City. In a CCTV footage, Ragos approached the policemen and started shouting due to their claim of him violating quarantine protocols. The police officers asked Ramos to go home and he allegedly attempted to pull out a .38 caliber hand gun from his sling bag prompting Florendo to shoot Ragos.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/258708-quezon-city-cop-faces-criminal-probe-killing-mentally-challenged-coronavirus-lockdown-violator|title=QC cop faces criminal probe for killing 'mentally challenged' lockdown violator|last=Talabong|first=Rambo|date=April 22, 2020|website=[[Rappler]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> Florendo shot Ragos twice, causing him to stagger. Ragos stood up, before falling to the ground. Ragos was brought to Commonwealth Hospital and was declared dead at 5:57 p.m.<ref name=\":2\" />  \n\nWitnesses claimed the victim did not have a gun inside his bag. Upon checking, police found it only carried his quarantine pass.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/4/23/retired-military-Winston-Ragos-Quezon-City-shooting-PNP-Gamboa.html|title=PNP chief says cop who shot ex-military only made 'judgment call', vows 'thorough' probe on incident|last=Rola|first=Alyssa|date=April 23, 2020|website=[[CNN Philippines]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> For the [[Philippine National Police]] (PNP), it was a \"judgment call\" for Florendo.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/metro/735211/pnp-cop-who-shot-army-vet-only-made-judgment-call/story/|title=PNP: Cop who shot army vet only made \u2018judgment call\u2019|last=Casilao|first=Joahna Lei|date=April 23, 2020|website=GMA News Online|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n== Reactions ==\nHis death during the quarantine period led to heavy criticism to the PNP. Florendo surrendered to authorities and yielded his service firearm.<ref name=\":3\" /> Senator [[Risa Hontiveros]] asked the human rights sector and the police to investigate his death and said in a Facebook post that law enforcement agencies do not have an excuse on brutality and violence towards persons with mental illness and the powerless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1263137/hontiveros-wants-chr-pnp-to-probe-death-of-ex-soldier-in-quezon-city|title=Hontiveros wants CHR, PNP to probe death of ex-soldier in Quezon City|last=Lalu|first=Gabriel Pabico|date=April 22, 2020|website=newsinfo.inquirer.net|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> A hashtag named #JusticeForWinstonRagos trended online.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/hashtag/JusticeForWinstonRagos|title=#JusticeForWinstonRagos hashtag on Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> The Quezon City government released a statement online on their stance as the Quezon City Police Department is undertaking a thorough investigation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/QCGov/status/1252990477114073088|title=Statement of the Quezon City Government on the Brgy. Pasong Putik incident|last=Government|first=Quezon City|date=2020-04-22|website=@QCGov|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> The Makabayan bloc of the House of Representatives has condemned the shooting saying the incident \u201chighlights the draconian handling\u201d of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|coronavirus crisis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1263389/makabayan-bloc-condemns-shooting-of-ex-soldier-at-qc-checkpoint|title=Makabayan bloc condemns shooting of ex-soldier at QC checkpoint|last=Mercado|first=Neil Arwin|website=newsinfo.inquirer.net|langu